def: One skilled in the use or construction of stereoscopes.
Having unlucky omens; inauspicious. See Note under Ill, adv.
To flatter in a servile way. Byron.
A proud or haughty person. Sylvester.
Habitually silent; not given to converse; not apt to talk orspeak.-- Tac"i*turn*ly, adv.
To walk or run about in a slatternly, careless, or thoughtlessmanner. [Colloq.] Pope.
A native or inhabitant of Cyprus.
Shaped like a boat; (Bot.) elongated and having the uppersurface decidedly concave, as the glumes of many grasses.
A liquid measure equal to four gills, or an imperial pint.[Scot.]
The quality of that which is fungous; fungous excrescence.Dunglison.
